Summary

A  Gender  Equality  Gap  Report  which  details  Dover  District  Council’s  gender  pay 
position as at 31 March 2017 must be published by 30 March 2018. It must then be 
reported  &  published  at  least  annually  and  the  information  held  for  3  years.  This 
statement  is  prepared  to  comply  with  the  requirements  of  the  Equality  Act  2010 
(Specific Duties and Public Authorities) Regulations 2017.  

Introduction and Background
The Equality Act 2010 (Specific Duties and Public Authorities) Regulations 2017 (the 
Regulations) require the Council to publish its Gender Pay Gap Report by 30 March 
2018.  This  is  a  matter  for  the  Executive  and  is  presented  for  approval  prior  to 
publication. 

A  relevant  public  authority  must  publish,  for  2017  and  each  subsequent  year,  the 
following information:

