Identification of Options

The Council is required by law to publish this information by 30 March 2018. 

Evaluation of Options

This is the only option. To fail to publish the data would be unlawful. This approach 
meets the requirement of the regulations.

Resource Implications
There are no additional resource implications 

Corporate Implications

Comment from the Section 151 Officer: Accountancy have been consulted and have 
no further comment to add (VB)

Comment  from  the  Solicitor  to  the  Council:  The  Head  of  Legal  Services  has  been 
consulted during the preparation of this report and has no further comment to add.

Comment from the Equalities Officer:  The gender pay gap noted within this report is 
not the result of the Council failing to pay men and women equally, but is due to the 
distribution of men and women within the organisation. Members are reminded that in 
discharging  their  responsibilities  they  are  required  to  comply  with  the  public  sector 
equality  duty  as  set  out 
the  Equality  Act  2010 
